Wash and dry produce.

Toast @sourdough bread{4%slices} in a #toaster{}.

Slice tops and bottoms off @orange{2}. Using a small sharp #knife{}, slice off
peel and white pith; discard. Halve oranges lengthwise, then thinly slice
into half-moons. Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @fig jam{2%tbsp} and @crème fraîche{10%tbsp}.

In a second small microwave-safe bowl, combine half the @maple syrup{2%tbsp}
and @butter{2%tbsp}. Microwave until softened, ~{15-30%seconds}. Stir to combine.

Spread as much maple butter over toasted bread as you like. Spread
with remaining crème fraîche and top with orange slices. Sprinkle with
a pinch of @cinnamon{1%tsp}. Drizzle with as much remaining maple syrup as
you like.

Divide maple butter cinnamon toast between plates and serve with
apple slices and creamy fig dip on the side.

> This 15-minute breakfast delivers on fun for kids of all ages, and is super-easy on their grown-ups (plus no pots or pans to clean up!). After all, we've never heard a parent say "I don't need more time in the morning."